                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>Twelve lines of Latin text. The text takes up the entirety of the face of the stone. The majority of the text is centred, however the "et" on line 7 is on the far right of an otherwise blank line and the name Alypus on line 11 is aligned to the left of the stone.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                    <damage/>
                                </layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>The handwriting is neat and serifed, and the kerning is fairly even. The size of the letters varies between lines. The text on the first four and bottom two lines are larger than the lines in the middle of the stone. The A and U of Augustalis on lines 5 and 10 are in ligature.</p>
